{
  "texts": [
    "Electra, however, introduces a more efficient method called replaced token detection.",
    "Unlike BERT, Electra replaces some tokens with plausible alternatives from a smaller generator network, and a discriminative model is trained to identify whether each token in the input has been replaced or not.",
    "The generator part in Electra assigns probabilities to the generation of specific tokens x t using a softmax layer [14].",
    "FLAN-T5FLAN-T5, 7 an extension of the Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer (T5) model [57], represents a significant advancement in NLP.",
    "Developed for instruction fine-tuning, FLAN-T5 is trained across various tasks, enhancing its adaptability and efficiency in text-to-text operations [13]."
  ]
}